; judged-trust.fk — trust over fear, JUDGED: the gate the Memora ingest lived, named as law.
; Offered 2026-07-04 by Urs in three words: "trust over fear (judged)". The refinement it adds to the
; ingest door: trust and fear are EQUALS before judgment — neither stance earns anything by itself.
; Judgment (the adversarial pass; the primary read; the skeptic's default) is the hinge:
;   - JUDGED trust may FREEZE into body            (today: the three convergences that froze)
;   - JUDGED fear is WITNESSED — seen, never ice   (today: the retrieval gap, the mirror)
;   - UNJUDGED trust is CREDULITY and composts     (today: "the body already does cue anchors")
;   - UNJUDGED fear is a FALSE ALARM and composts  (today: the suspected-hallucinated author list)
; Trust outranks fear only on the far side of the judge; on the near side they compost together.
; Concord with knowledge-ingest (the same three-verdict door on different hinges): judged trust lands
; where deep+fear-free lands (2), judged fear where deep+fearful lands (1), unjudged where shallow
; lands (0) — proven in the band, not asserted.
; Honest floor: stance/judged are scalars modeling the real senses (text-frequency's fear<->love read;
; the adversarial verify pass); the GATE LOGIC is the shape.
;
; Self-contained over core. Four-way by tests/judged-trust-band.fk.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk

(do
    (defn jt-stance (u) (head u))                    ; 1 = trust, 0 = fear
    (defn jt-judged? (u) (head (tail u)))            ; 1 = stood before the judge (adversarial verify / primary read)
    (defn jt-verdict (u)                             ; 2 = frozen (body) / 1 = witnessed (liquid) / 0 = composted
        (if (eq (jt-judged? u) 0) 0
            (if (eq (jt-stance u) 1) 2 1)))

    (defn jtk (cond bit) (if cond bit 0))
    (defn judged-trust-check ()
        (add (add (add (add
            (jtk (eq (jt-verdict (list 1 1)) 2) 1)        ; judged trust -> FROZEN (trust, on the far side of the judge, becomes body)
            (jtk (eq (jt-verdict (list 0 1)) 1) 10))      ; judged fear -> WITNESSED (fear is seen, never load-bearing)
            (jtk (eq (jt-verdict (list 1 0)) 0) 100))     ; unjudged trust is CREDULITY -> composts
            (jtk (eq (jt-verdict (list 0 0)) 0) 1000))    ; unjudged fear is a FALSE ALARM -> composts
            (jtk (gt (jt-verdict (list 1 1)) (jt-verdict (list 0 1))) 10000)))  ; trust OVER fear -- but only judged trust outranks judged fear
)
